518
00:46:54,792 --> 00:46:56,521
It was the General.

519
00:46:56,560 --> 00:46:58,528
- The guy who...
- Yeah.

520
00:46:58,562 --> 00:47:00,723
He was driving the other car.

521
00:47:00,764 --> 00:47:04,825
So yeah, I can't really feel too bad
about him getting beat up.

522
00:48:04,428 --> 00:48:06,896
My old house.

523
00:48:06,931 --> 00:48:09,661
I didn't spend much time
at my house that summer.

524
00:48:09,700 --> 00:48:13,136
I'd camp out at Jackson's
most of the time.

525
00:48:13,170 --> 00:48:15,832
That's what summers are for.

526
00:48:15,873 --> 00:48:20,310
But for everyone there's a time
when you return home

527
00:48:20,344 --> 00:48:22,403
and it just doesn't
feel like home anymore.

528
00:48:22,446 --> 00:48:26,439
Maybe you've been gone
a day, week, years,

529
00:48:26,483 --> 00:48:28,815
but it just doesn't feel like home.

530
00:49:00,150 --> 00:49:02,015
Brock?

531
00:49:05,289 --> 00:49:08,781
Hey, Brock, your coach called...

532
00:49:26,610 --> 00:49:29,738
Philip Walden steps up
to the plate,

533
00:49:29,780 --> 00:49:32,305
gets ready, and he swings!

534
00:49:32,349 --> 00:49:35,750
Oh, strike one!

535
00:49:37,288 --> 00:49:40,314
Okay, he gets set.

536
00:49:40,357 --> 00:49:43,520
Swings again...

537
00:49:43,560 --> 00:49:44,549
Why'd you have to go and do that?

538
00:49:44,595 --> 00:49:45,823
You shouldn't have done that.

539
00:49:45,863 --> 00:49:48,991
We're just having a little fun...

540
00:49:53,370 --> 00:49:56,168
Phil. Hey, what's up, man?

541
00:49:56,206 --> 00:49:58,640
Brock?

542
00:49:58,676 --> 00:50:00,405
Yeah, what do you want?

543
00:50:02,813 --> 00:50:04,610
Brock, how did you get this?

544
00:50:04,648 --> 00:50:06,946
The bat?

545
00:50:06,984 --> 00:50:10,283
Dad gave it to me when I was,
like, two or something.

546
00:50:10,321 --> 00:50:12,482
Do you want it?

547
00:50:12,523 --> 00:50:14,514
If you want it,
it's yours.

548
00:50:14,558 --> 00:50:15,752
Brock, I was there.

549
00:50:15,793 --> 00:50:17,988
What are you talking about?

550
00:50:18,028 --> 00:50:20,826
Jackson and I
saw the whole thing.

551
00:50:20,864 --> 00:50:24,800
What, a game or something?

552
00:50:24,835 --> 00:50:29,670
This is the bat!
You beat the General with this bat!

553
00:50:39,650 --> 00:50:40,947
Right?

554
00:50:47,658 --> 00:50:50,252
- It's not my fault.
- Brock, don't lie to me.

555
00:50:50,294 --> 00:50:53,695
The General came at us
with a shotgun.

556
00:50:53,731 --> 00:50:55,699
- Don't lie to me.
- He was gonna kill us.

557
00:50:55,733 --> 00:50:59,191
He broke Chip's car
and he had a shotgun

558
00:50:59,236 --> 00:51:01,170
and he was going to kill...
Phil, look at me.

559
00:51:01,205 --> 00:51:03,765
Phil, he was gonna kill us.

560
00:51:03,807 --> 00:51:05,172
He was going to kill us.

561
00:51:05,209 --> 00:51:08,042
Besides, you know what he
did to Jackson's family.

562
00:51:08,078 --> 00:51:11,070
Keep this between us, Phil.

563
00:51:11,115 --> 00:51:13,276
- Here you go.
- Phil.

564
00:51:33,737 --> 00:51:36,865
- Hey, Jackson.
- Hey.

565
00:51:36,907 --> 00:51:39,239
I've been looking for you.

566
00:51:39,276 --> 00:51:43,144
- Nobody can find Camille.
- What?

567
00:51:43,180 --> 00:51:46,013
Her mom said

568
00:51:46,049 --> 00:51:47,573
she hasn't been home in days,

569
00:51:47,618 --> 00:51:49,711
and she never came over
the other night.

570
00:51:49,753 --> 00:51:53,018
- Maybe she just...
- No.

571
00:51:53,056 --> 00:51:57,584
She left a note at church.

572
00:51:57,628 --> 00:51:59,892
- She did?
- Yeah.

573
00:51:59,930 --> 00:52:03,127
So she came to see you last night,
gave you the note?

574
00:52:03,167 --> 00:52:05,692
No, I found the note by the altar.

575
00:52:07,738 --> 00:52:11,139
- It's hers.
- Pastor, we don't know that.

576
00:52:11,175 --> 00:52:12,802
Yeah, we do.

577
00:52:12,843 --> 00:52:15,641
- It could be a forgery.
- It's not.

578
00:52:15,679 --> 00:52:17,340
I'll be damned if I'm
gonna tell her mother

579
00:52:17,381 --> 00:52:19,906
until I know
this is something.

580
00:52:19,950 --> 00:52:22,942
Lem, she does clerical work
here sometimes.

581
00:52:22,986 --> 00:52:23,975
I can go to the office

582
00:52:24,021 --> 00:52:26,012
and get you a sample
of her handwriting right now.

583
00:52:26,056 --> 00:52:29,924
"Pastor Salem, I've made a decision

584
00:52:29,960 --> 00:52:31,723
and I know you'll listen.

585
00:52:31,762 --> 00:52:34,925
I've been thinking about
where my life is going,

586
00:52:34,965 --> 00:52:36,990
where the life of my child will go,

587
00:52:37,034 --> 00:52:40,265
and the thing is I think
I need to start over. "

588
00:52:41,972 --> 00:52:45,066
She was pregnant?
You're sure?

589
00:52:45,108 --> 00:52:47,576
Yeah. She told me.

590
00:52:47,611 --> 00:52:49,772
"No one needs to know.

591
00:52:49,813 --> 00:52:52,509
This is my last chance
to live a normal life

592
00:52:52,549 --> 00:52:56,076
before I have to take on
this huge responsibility,

593
00:52:56,119 --> 00:52:58,610
so I'm starting over.

594
00:52:58,655 --> 00:53:00,748
It's the beginning of a new life.

595
00:53:00,791 --> 00:53:03,589
I will be the mother
God wants me to be.

596
00:53:03,627 --> 00:53:06,721
Thank you for everything,
Camille. "

597
00:53:06,763 --> 00:53:10,665
- When?
- In the last week.

598
00:53:10,701 --> 00:53:11,998
She had just found out.

599
00:53:12,035 --> 00:53:13,525
She see Doc about it?

600
00:53:13,570 --> 00:53:18,269
Not to my knowledge.
She didn't want anybody to know.

601
00:53:18,308 --> 00:53:21,277
- She say who the father was?
- No.

602
00:53:21,311 --> 00:53:24,872
She never told me, and, um,

603
00:53:24,915 --> 00:53:27,042
- I never asked.
- Sorry, Pastor.

604
00:53:27,084 --> 00:53:32,181
Jackson, there's something
I need to tell you about my brother.

605
00:55:17,427 --> 00:55:19,190
Pastor Salem.

606
00:55:21,498 --> 00:55:24,092
- Hey, Lem.
- Hey.

607
00:55:24,134 --> 00:55:26,432
I wonder if we could trouble you
to borrow that ladder of yours.

608
00:55:26,470 --> 00:55:29,064
- Frank's just about gave way.
- Yeah, no problem.

609
00:55:29,106 --> 00:55:33,566
- Having a little problem there?
- Yeah, wouldn't you know it,

610
00:55:33,610 --> 00:55:36,443
thorns coming up in the garden
just before the big to-do.

611
00:55:36,480 --> 00:55:39,347
Oh yeah, those crows drop
those seeds in the worst places.

612
00:55:39,383 --> 00:55:41,374
Yeah, they do.

613
00:55:44,221 --> 00:55:48,681
Um, listen, Pastor.

614
00:55:48,725 --> 00:55:51,159
I've been talking with Camille's mom.

615
00:55:51,194 --> 00:55:54,755
Naturally she's in a real tizzy

616
00:55:54,798 --> 00:55:56,993
about this whole deal,

617
00:55:57,034 --> 00:56:00,470
looking for someone to blame.

618
00:56:00,504 --> 00:56:03,803
So if there's anything you know...

619
00:56:03,840 --> 00:56:06,138
I told you, Lem. She didn't
tell me where she was going.

620
00:56:08,245 --> 00:56:11,305
The last thing she would have
wanted is for her name...

621
00:56:13,750 --> 00:56:16,184
She didn't want to wear
the red letter, Lem,

622
00:56:16,219 --> 00:56:21,156
not in the midst
of all this celebration.

623
00:56:21,191 --> 00:56:22,783
Yeah.

624
00:56:24,094 --> 00:56:26,824
I guess you're right.

625
00:56:27,831 --> 00:56:31,028
Yeah, I'll wait until things
simmer down a little bit.

626
00:56:31,068 --> 00:56:34,799
But once this celebration is over...

627
00:56:36,640 --> 00:56:38,130
something.

628
00:56:40,444 --> 00:56:44,471
You know, she's even trying
to blame that Eli Cottonmouth.

629
00:56:44,514 --> 00:56:49,713
Well, it's easy to point fingers
at the stranger, don't you think?

630
00:56:49,753 --> 00:56:51,220
Hmm.

631
00:56:51,254 --> 00:56:52,778
Yes it is.

632
00:56:52,823 --> 00:56:55,986
What do you suppose
he's up to in there?

633
00:56:56,026 --> 00:56:58,893
Who knows? I guess
we'll find out soon enough.

634
00:56:58,929 --> 00:57:00,487
Yeah, I guess we will.

635
00:57:00,530 --> 00:57:03,522
I'll see you tonight, Pastor.
I'm gonna help myself to that ladder.

636
00:57:03,567 --> 00:57:04,864
Absolutely.
It's around back.

637
00:57:30,193 --> 00:57:31,785
It's a mighty pretty church
you got here.

638
00:57:34,164 --> 00:57:37,099
I like churches...

639
00:57:37,134 --> 00:57:41,127
old churches where the air
is heavy with God.

640
00:57:42,139 --> 00:57:46,576
Well, this one is pretty old.

641
00:57:46,610 --> 00:57:49,272
They say you can't judge a book
by its cover, can you, Pastor?

642
00:57:51,414 --> 00:57:53,211
What are you doing?

643
00:57:54,618 --> 00:57:59,578
Digging. These buildings
tell me stories,

644
00:57:59,623 --> 00:58:03,218
and I guess that's why
I do what I do.

645
00:58:03,260 --> 00:58:06,161
And what is that, exactly?
Intimidate people?

646
00:58:09,733 --> 00:58:12,429
Who are you trying to impress?

647
00:58:12,469 --> 00:58:14,369
There's no royalty here.

648
00:58:15,872 --> 00:58:19,535
Why did you choose this town?

649
00:58:19,576 --> 00:58:21,840
As I recall, this town chose me.

650
00:58:26,249 --> 00:58:28,979
God, after all, spoke through

651
00:58:29,019 --> 00:58:31,749
the hands of a modest carpenter.

652
00:59:07,324 --> 00:59:08,882
Philip.

653
00:59:08,925 --> 00:59:10,153
Philip, stop.

654
00:59:10,193 --> 00:59:12,627
- Phil...
- Let me go!

655
00:59:12,662 --> 00:59:14,129
Philip listen...

656
00:59:14,164 --> 00:59:16,758
- where are you taking that?
- Sheriff Baker.

657
00:59:16,800 --> 00:59:19,166
No no no no no. No, listen.

658
00:59:19,202 --> 00:59:20,464
Just listen to me for a second.

659
00:59:20,503 --> 00:59:22,994
- The General is...
- Where's Camille?

660
00:59:23,039 --> 00:59:26,531
- Camille? What does Camille...
- She was supposed to meet you.

661
00:59:26,576 --> 00:59:29,909
- And then she disappeared!
- Whoa whoa.

662
00:59:29,946 --> 00:59:32,073
Are you saying that you
think I did something...

663
00:59:32,115 --> 00:59:35,516
Brock, what did you do to her?

664
00:59:35,552 --> 00:59:38,783
- She never showed.
- Brock, come on.

665
00:59:38,822 --> 00:59:40,722
She never showed up, man.

666
00:59:40,757 --> 00:59:43,749
Phil, I don't know
what you think I am...

667
00:59:43,793 --> 00:59:47,422
You did it once.
She was supposed to meet you.

668
00:59:47,464 --> 00:59:50,991
She was excited and dressed up
and going to meet you.

669
00:59:51,034 --> 00:59:52,763
And no one ever saw her again!

670
00:59:52,802 --> 00:59:56,568
She never showed up, man.
She stood me up.

671
00:59:56,606 --> 00:59:58,335
I have no id...
look at me!

672
00:59:58,375 --> 01:00:00,843
I have no idea
what happened to Camille.

673
01:00:00,877 --> 01:00:03,573
People are saying that she
ran away or something.

674
01:00:05,849 --> 01:00:09,046
Philip, I'm your brother, yeah?

675
01:00:09,085 --> 01:00:12,543
Philly.

676
01:00:14,958 --> 01:00:17,222
Say something.

677
01:01:04,941 --> 01:01:07,273
Okay, it's all done.
Can I go now?

678
01:01:07,310 --> 01:01:08,937
Hang on there, sport.

679
01:01:08,979 --> 01:01:11,504
Dad, I told Philip I was
going to meet him.

680
01:01:11,548 --> 01:01:13,482
Yeah, okay.

681
01:01:13,516 --> 01:01:16,679
I just need you
to do something first.

682
01:01:16,720 --> 01:01:19,211
Dad.

683
01:01:19,255 --> 01:01:22,486
Jackson, Camille is not around

684
01:01:22,525 --> 01:01:24,220
and I need you to pick up the slack.

685
01:01:24,260 --> 01:01:25,693
Okay, what?

686
01:01:29,432 --> 01:01:34,267
There's a box
on the kitchen counter.

687
01:01:34,304 --> 01:01:35,862
What is it?

688
01:01:35,905 --> 01:01:39,500
- It's a care package for the General.
- What? Why?

689
01:01:42,545 --> 01:01:47,039
Well, he got beat up pretty bad.

690
01:01:47,083 --> 01:01:51,019
- It's the right thing to do.
- No.

691
01:01:51,054 --> 01:01:53,818
What was that?

692
01:01:53,857 --> 01:01:56,121
No, I won't do it.

693
01:01:56,159 --> 01:01:59,560
He got what he deserved
and now he has to live with it.

694
01:01:59,596 --> 01:02:02,360
Jackson, don't
say things like that.

695
01:02:06,036 --> 01:02:08,300
Look, son, sit down a second.

696
01:02:08,338 --> 01:02:10,101
Let me tell you something.

697
01:02:16,579 --> 01:02:19,139
You know when I started
to go blind?

698
01:02:19,182 --> 01:02:21,150
Yeah, it was after the accident.

699
01:02:23,420 --> 01:02:27,516
- No.
- What do you mean?

700
01:02:30,260 --> 01:02:34,196
I was losing my eyesight

701
01:02:34,230 --> 01:02:35,663
a little bit before then.

702
01:02:35,698 --> 01:02:38,394
I was having these spells,

703
01:02:38,435 --> 01:02:43,031
and uh, and sort of like
tunneling around the edges.

704
01:02:44,841 --> 01:02:47,139
I didn't tell anybody.

705
01:02:47,177 --> 01:02:49,145
I figured

706
01:02:49,179 --> 01:02:52,512
if I didn't talk about it,

707
01:02:52,549 --> 01:02:54,676
it wasn't really happening.

708
01:02:54,717 --> 01:02:59,654
The accident...

709
01:02:59,689 --> 01:03:01,418
it wasn't the General's fault.

710
01:03:06,529 --> 01:03:08,463
It was my fault.

711
01:03:08,498 --> 01:03:11,399
- What were you doing?
- Jackson...

712
01:03:11,434 --> 01:03:15,268
No, what were you doing driving
the car if you couldn't see?

713
01:03:15,305 --> 01:03:18,138
- It came in spells.
- I don't care.

714
01:03:18,174 --> 01:03:23,134
Jackson, don't you hate me.
I hate myself enough.

715
01:03:23,179 --> 01:03:26,148
- Good.
- This is about the General.

716
01:03:26,182 --> 01:03:28,582
He didn't do anything to us.

717
01:03:28,618 --> 01:03:31,314
And now he needs our help.

718
01:03:31,354 --> 01:03:36,291
Deliver this package yourself.
You stand in front of him

719
01:03:36,326 --> 01:03:39,352
and tell him
what you just told me.

720
01:03:39,395 --> 01:03:41,693
- You killed her!
- Hey!

721
01:03:41,731 --> 01:03:43,756
Everything is on you!

722
01:03:43,800 --> 01:03:45,791
Jackson, what are you doing?

723
01:03:45,835 --> 01:03:49,703
You destroy everything you touch.

724
01:03:49,739 --> 01:03:51,639
So I'm making sure
you can't touch me.

725
01:03:51,674 --> 01:03:53,369
Jackson!

726
01:04:26,176 --> 01:04:29,168
- Hey.
- Hey.

727
01:05:22,732 --> 01:05:25,166
The story of that summer...

728
01:05:25,201 --> 01:05:27,192
the knowledge was always there.

729
01:05:27,237 --> 01:05:31,230
Eli just had to hand us the fruit.

730
01:05:31,274 --> 01:05:34,266
And you saw
what you needed to see.

731
01:05:36,980 --> 01:05:39,210
One,

732
01:05:39,249 --> 01:05:42,082
two,

733
01:05:42,118 --> 01:05:44,052
three...

734
01:05:48,091 --> 01:05:50,116
What is it
that boys have in their hearts

735
01:05:50,159 --> 01:05:52,457
that lets them
see things men can't?

736
01:05:54,864 --> 01:05:57,833
When did they lose it?

737
01:05:59,068 --> 01:06:03,027
This town and I...
we were young,

738
01:06:03,072 --> 01:06:05,233
just boys in those days.

739
01:06:05,275 --> 01:06:09,234
But boys grow up.

740
01:06:09,279 --> 01:06:11,907
Do you think he exists?

741
01:06:11,948 --> 01:06:14,678
I don't know.

742
01:06:14,717 --> 01:06:17,185
I like to think he does.

743
01:06:17,220 --> 01:06:22,055
But if you listen to everyone else
they'll say he's just a story.

744
01:06:22,091 --> 01:06:23,786
I thought that's what it was,

745
01:06:23,826 --> 01:06:27,523
- to keep us kids in at night.
- Yeah.

746
01:06:27,563 --> 01:06:28,928
Two-Legged Alligator Man is real.

747
01:06:28,965 --> 01:06:31,593
Jackson.

748
01:06:31,634 --> 01:06:35,365
We'll get a picture of him one day.

749
01:06:35,405 --> 01:06:38,340
Close your eyes, count to three.

750
01:06:43,613 --> 01:06:44,602
One...

751
01:06:49,519 --> 01:06:51,146
...two...

752
01:06:54,390 --> 01:06:56,551
...three!

753
01:07:00,263 --> 01:07:01,287
Jackson!

754
01:07:03,199 --> 01:07:04,530
Come on, Jackson.

755
01:07:19,682 --> 01:07:20,706
Jackson!

756
01:07:42,772 --> 01:07:43,966
Jackson!

757
01:08:26,048 --> 01:08:28,209
And just like that,

758
01:08:28,251 --> 01:08:31,448
the world was meaningless,

759
01:08:31,487 --> 01:08:35,150
a gift from Eli.

760
01:08:35,191 --> 01:08:39,218
Because as I watched
my best friend die,

761
01:08:39,262 --> 01:08:42,231
the town was here,

762
01:08:42,265 --> 01:08:45,200
all caught up in the
excitement of that model.

763
01:09:07,957 --> 01:09:09,982
Has anyone here seen Eli?

764
01:09:10,026 --> 01:09:13,325
I don't think so.
I haven't seen him.

765
01:09:23,539 --> 01:09:25,905
Well, folks, I know you all

766
01:09:25,942 --> 01:09:28,604
have been
looking forward to this,

767
01:09:28,644 --> 01:09:32,978
the chance to see our
little paradise immortalized.

768
01:09:33,015 --> 01:09:36,644
Now some may call it vanity,

769
01:09:36,686 --> 01:09:40,918
but I say we got quite
a bit to be proud of.

770
01:09:40,957 --> 01:09:42,925
Yes, sir.

771
01:09:42,959 --> 01:09:46,918
We got us a mighty pretty town,

772
01:09:46,963 --> 01:09:50,729
a mighty pretty town
indeed, folks.

773
01:09:50,766 --> 01:09:54,725
So, without further ado...

774
01:10:54,330 --> 01:10:58,061
He was just a petty con man

775
01:10:58,100 --> 01:11:01,729
with a sense of humor.

776
01:11:01,771 --> 01:11:03,966
Beautiful little town, right?

777
01:12:16,012 --> 01:12:19,004
No no, Pastor. It's Eli.
We'll get him for this,

778
01:12:19,048 --> 01:12:23,007
I promise you. It's all right.

779
01:12:23,052 --> 01:12:26,783
No. No.

780
01:12:26,822 --> 01:12:29,791
He's right.

781
01:12:31,460 --> 01:12:32,688
It's us.

782
01:12:36,399 --> 01:12:38,094
It's us.

783
01:12:39,869 --> 01:12:43,703
God bless him for showing us.
It's us.

784
01:12:45,875 --> 01:12:50,835
It's me. It's me!

785
01:13:02,191 --> 01:13:05,092
She was my love.

786
01:13:05,127 --> 01:13:07,755
She was my sin.

787
01:13:49,105 --> 01:13:52,597
Cursed is the ground
because of you.

788
01:13:52,641 --> 01:13:55,906
It will produce
thistles and thorns

789
01:13:55,945 --> 01:13:59,142
because of you!

790
01:14:02,351 --> 01:14:05,787
Oh, Jesus!

791
01:14:39,922 --> 01:14:41,913
Take me.

792
01:14:41,957 --> 01:14:44,425
Take me!

793
01:15:15,391 --> 01:15:18,485
His model...

794
01:15:18,527 --> 01:15:22,623
it's a mirror that only reflects
the darkest parts of yourself.

795
01:15:26,735 --> 01:15:30,296
Paradise can't exist
with the knowledge of sin,

796
01:15:30,339 --> 01:15:33,536
and Eli threw it in our faces.

797
01:15:35,444 --> 01:15:37,878
This was no Eden.

798
01:15:40,683 --> 01:15:42,981
How could we live
with each other now?

799
01:16:30,633 --> 01:16:33,158
Yeah, it's just a model,

800
01:16:33,202 --> 01:16:36,603
but I can barely
stand to look at it.

801
01:16:40,109 --> 01:16:44,045
Because if I look too hard,

802
01:16:44,079 --> 01:16:48,038
I can see myself,
empty.

803
01:17:32,127 --> 01:17:34,118
Hello, Philip.

804
01:17:38,100 --> 01:17:39,965
Hi.

805
01:17:40,002 --> 01:17:41,993
Can I get you something?

806
01:17:42,037 --> 01:17:45,165
No, I...
I was...

807
01:17:45,207 --> 01:17:46,799
I saw the sign, and I just...

808
01:17:46,842 --> 01:17:51,438
Oh, hon, I am so
sorry about Jackson.

809
01:17:53,515 --> 01:17:56,279
Why are you still here?

810
01:17:56,318 --> 01:17:58,479
Well, this is my home.

811
01:17:58,520 --> 01:18:01,751
There's no one here,
Miss Rockwell.

812
01:18:01,790 --> 01:18:04,657
There's no power...

813
01:18:04,693 --> 01:18:06,558
here, anywhere in the town,

814
01:18:06,595 --> 01:18:10,258
so I don't know how you're doing
this whole thing with the light...

815
01:18:10,299 --> 01:18:13,359
It's all a little impossible.

816
01:18:43,799 --> 01:18:46,563
- Hey.
- Hey.

817
01:18:50,372 --> 01:18:53,830
Double vanilla milkshake,
extra strawberry syrup?

818
01:18:53,876 --> 01:18:55,434
Yep.

819
01:18:58,480 --> 01:19:01,347
I used to like those.

820
01:19:01,383 --> 01:19:03,112
What happened?

821
01:19:07,122 --> 01:19:10,819
I guess I grew up.

822
01:19:10,859 --> 01:19:12,827
What do you do?

823
01:19:12,861 --> 01:19:16,228
I work for the
power authority now.

824
01:19:17,966 --> 01:19:19,490
You know, we're gonna
flood this town.

825
01:19:19,535 --> 01:19:21,799
They're flooding it?

826
01:19:21,837 --> 01:19:24,203
Yep.

827
01:19:24,239 --> 01:19:27,072
In 24 hours this
will all be underwater.

828
01:19:27,109 --> 01:19:31,910
The Two-Legged Alligator Man's
gonna like that just fine.

829
01:19:34,383 --> 01:19:36,408
Do you believe in him now?

830
01:19:41,023 --> 01:19:44,584
It's taken a while, but I came back
to try and make sense of it all.

831
01:19:47,596 --> 01:19:50,963
To be honest with you,
I think I'm still just as confused.

832
01:19:50,999 --> 01:19:53,524
And?

833
01:19:57,339 --> 01:19:59,398
L...

834
01:19:59,441 --> 01:20:02,035
I don't know.

835
01:20:02,077 --> 01:20:05,672
You've lived in this town
your whole life,

836
01:20:05,714 --> 01:20:08,308
and it was beautiful.

837
01:20:08,350 --> 01:20:12,286
But that's not the real world.

838
01:20:12,321 --> 01:20:16,985
The real word will eat you,

839
01:20:17,025 --> 01:20:20,586
like the Two-Legged Alligator Man.

840
01:20:20,629 --> 01:20:23,257
Isn't that what Eli
wanted to tell us?

841
01:20:24,733 --> 01:20:28,897
It's easy to believe in things
in a place like this.

842
01:20:28,937 --> 01:20:32,930
But the world out there...

843
01:20:32,975 --> 01:20:35,375
doesn't make it so easy, does it?

844
01:20:35,410 --> 01:20:37,935
Maybe that's why you have to...

845
01:20:40,582 --> 01:20:42,345
believe in things.

846
01:20:47,356 --> 01:20:49,881
You may be onto something
there, kiddo.

847
01:20:54,296 --> 01:20:57,026
But I don't know what happened
to that part of me.

848
01:21:08,177 --> 01:21:13,240
Maybe I can come
with you this time.

849
01:21:17,853 --> 01:21:22,415
Yeah. Yeah, let's do that.

850
01:22:30,892 --> 01:22:32,860
There you are.

851
01:22:41,470 --> 01:22:43,768
You were right, Jackson!

